HEADWORD: handcolor
<hw>handcolor</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to add color to (a
black-and-white image) using an instrument held in the hand; <as>as,
Some old photographs are <ex>handcolored</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> color by hand.</syn>⟦br⟧
